{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 09 · Geometry & Orientation Effects — BRDF Reality Check\n",
    "\n",
    "Assess how viewing angle influences the occupancy → Chrom_total mapping. We compare linear fits \n",
    "for individual orientations (12 vs 6 o'clock) against the Σ aggregate, reproducing the ordering \n",
    "described on thesis p.39 (12 o'clock tighter fit, Σ most orientation-agnostic)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Inputs\n",
    "- `data/reference/mamba_ssm/denoised_full_run.csv` — denoised spectra by orientation.\n",
    "- `data/reference/reflectance/wavelength_grid.npy` — wavelength grid.\n",
    "- `data/raw/initial_calibration/DAD_to_Concentration_AUC/treatments_corrected_amounts.csv` — Chrom_total mg·gDW⁻¹ per sample.\n",
    "- `data/reference/initial_calibration/sample_id_truth.csv` — sample → treatment mapping." 
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from __future__ import annotations\n",
    "\n",
    "import re\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "PROJECT_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\n",
    "REFLECTANCE_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / 'data' / 'reference' / 'reflectance'\n",
    "MAMBA_REF_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / 'data' / 'reference' / 'mamba_ssm'\n",
    "STAGE_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / 'data' / 'raw' / 'initial_calibration' / 'DAD_to_Concentration_AUC'\n",
    "TRUTH_PATH = PROJECT_ROOT / 'data' / 'reference' / 'initial_calibration' / 'sample_id_truth.csv'\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.set_theme(style='whitegrid', context='talk')\n",
    "(REFLECTANCE_DIR / 'wavelength_grid.npy', MAMBA_REF_DIR / 'denoised_full_run.csv')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "wavelengths = np.load(REFLECTANCE_DIR / 'wavelength_grid.npy')\n",
    "denoised = pd.read_csv(MAMBA_REF_DIR / 'denoised_full_run.csv')\n",
    "amounts = pd.read_csv(STAGE_DIR / 'treatments_corrected_amounts.csv')\n",
    "truth = pd.read_csv(TRUTH_PATH)\n",
    "\n",
    "wavelength_cols = [col for col in denoised.columns if col.startswith('reflectance_nm_')]\n",
    "numeric_wavelengths = np.array([float(col.split('_')[-1]) for col in wavelength_cols])\n",
    "denoised[['relative_path', 'treatment', 'angle']].head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Continuum Removal & Occupancy (reuse helpers)\n",
    "We borrow the functions from notebooks 05/08."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def continuum_removed(signal: np.ndarray, lam: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n",
    "    lam_min, lam_max = lam[0], lam[-1]\n",
    "    baseline = signal[0] + (signal[-1] - signal[0]) * (lam - lam_min) / (lam_max - lam_min)\n",
    "    cr = baseline - signal\n",
    "    return np.clip(cr, 0, None)\n",
    "\n",
    "def bowl_template(lam: np.ndarray, amplitude: float) -> np.ndarray:\n",
    "    lam_center = 0.5 * (lam[0] + lam[-1])\n",
    "    halfwidth = 0.5 * (lam[-1] - lam[0])\n",
    "    lam_norm = (lam - lam_center) / halfwidth\n",
    "    bowl = amplitude * np.clip(1 - lam_norm**2, 0, None)\n",
    "    return bowl\n",
    "\n",
    "def occupancy_ratio(signal: np.ndarray, lam: np.ndarray) -> float:\n",
    "    cr = continuum_removed(signal, lam)\n",
    "    if cr.max() <= 0:\n",
    "        return 0.0\n",
    "    bowl = bowl_template(lam, cr.max())\n",
    "    numerator = np.trapz(cr, lam)\n",
    "    denominator = np.trapz(bowl, lam)\n",
    "    return float(np.clip(numerator / denominator, 0, 1))\n",
    "\n",
    "WINDOW = (320.0, 480.0)  # focus on primary mapping window\n",
    "\n",
    "def compute_orientation_occupancies(df: pd.DataFrame) -> pd.DataFrame:\n",
    "    records = []\n",
    "    lam_mask = (numeric_wavelengths >= WINDOW[0]) & (numeric_wavelengths <= WINDOW[1])\n",
    "    lam = numeric_wavelengths[lam_mask]\n",
    "    for _, row in df.iterrows():\n",
    "        signal = row[wavelength_cols].to_numpy(dtype=float)[lam_mask]\n",
    "        occ = occupancy_ratio(signal, lam)\n",
    "        records.append({\n",
    "            'relative_path': row['relative_path'],\n",
    "            'treatment': row['treatment'],\n",
    "            'sample': row['sample'],\n",
    "            'angle': row['angle'],\n",
    "            'occupancy': occ,\n",
    "        })\n",
    "    return pd.DataFrame(records)\n",
    "\n",
    "orientation_occ = compute_orientation_occupancies(denoised)\n",
    "orientation_occ.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Aggregate Occupancies\n",
    "Compute: (a) per-orientation average (6 o'clock, 12 o'clock) and (b) Σ across all orientations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def extract_dose(label: str) -> int:\n",
    "    match = re.search(r'treatment_(\\d+)', label)\n",
    "    return int(match.group(1)) if match else -1\n",
    "\n",
    "orientation_occ['dose'] = orientation_occ['treatment'].map(extract_dose)\n",
    "\n",
    "six = orientation_occ[orientation_occ['angle'] == '6Oclock'].groupby('dose')['occupancy'].mean().rename('occ_6').reset_index()\n",
    "twelve = orientation_occ[orientation_occ['angle'] == '12Oclock'].groupby('dose')['occupancy'].mean().rename('occ_12').reset_index()\n",
    "sigma = orientation_occ.groupby('dose')['occupancy'].mean().rename('occ_sigma').reset_index()\n",
    "\n",
    "occupancy_dose = six.merge(twelve, on='dose').merge(sigma, on='dose')\n",
    "occupancy_dose.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Chrom_total Trimmed Means\n",
    "Reuse 20% trimmed mean to align with prior notebooks."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def trimmed_mean(values: np.ndarray, trim: float = 0.2) -> float:\n",
    "    values = np.sort(np.asarray(values, dtype=float))\n",
    "    n = values.size\n",
    "    k = int(np.floor(trim * n))\n",
    "    if n - 2 * k <= 0:\n",
    "        raise ValueError('Not enough observations after trimming')\n",
    "    return values[k:n-k].mean()\n",
    "\n",
    "amounts_total = amounts[amounts['form'] == 'total'].merge(truth[['sample_id', 'treatment']], on='sample_id', how='left')\n",
    "trimmed_totals = []\n",
    "for treatment, group in amounts_total.groupby('treatment'):\n",
    "    trimmed_totals.append({'dose': int(treatment.split('_')[-1]), 'chrom_total': trimmed_mean(group['amount_mg_per_gDW'].to_numpy(), trim=0.2)})\n",
    "trimmed_totals = pd.DataFrame(trimmed_totals)\n",
    "trimmed_totals.head()
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "data = occupancy_dose.merge(trimmed_totals, on='dose')\n",
    "data.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Fit Orientation-specific Models\n",
    "Fit linear regressions for 12 o'clock, 6 o'clock, and Σ (excluding dose 1). Report |r| and RMSE."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\n",
    "\n",
    "def fit_linear(df: pd.DataFrame, feature: str) -> dict[str, float]:\n",
    "    mask = df['dose'] != 1\n",
    "    x = df.loc[mask, feature].to_numpy().reshape(-1, 1)\n",
    "    y = df.loc[mask, 'chrom_total'].to_numpy()\n",
    "    model = LinearRegression().fit(x, y)\n",
    "    preds = model.predict(x)\n",
    "    residuals = y - preds\n",
    "    rmse = float(np.sqrt(np.mean(residuals ** 2)))\n",
    "    r = float(np.corrcoef(x.squeeze(), y)[0, 1])\n",
    "    return {\n",
    "        'feature': feature,\n",
    "        'slope': float(model.coef_[0]),\n",
    "        'intercept': float(model.intercept_),\n",
    "        'r': r,\n",
    "        'rmse': rmse,\n",
    "        'model': model,\n",
    "    }\n",
    "\n",
    "fits = [fit_linear(data, feature) for feature in ['occ_12', 'occ_6', 'occ_sigma']]\n",
    "pd.DataFrame([{k: v for k, v in d.items() if k != 'model'} for d in fits])\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Check ordering: we expect |r| (12 o'clock) > |r| (6 o'clock), Σ comparable or slightly better overall RMSE."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "for fit in fits:\n",
    "    print(f"{fit['feature']}: |r|={abs(fit['r']):.3f}, RMSE={fit['rmse']:.3f}")\n",
    ""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Visualise Orientation Scatter\n",
    "Plot occupancy vs Chrom_total for each orientation to highlight geometry effects."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(15, 5), sharey=True)\n",
    "for ax, feature, title in zip(axes, ['occ_12', 'occ_6', 'occ_sigma'], ['12 o\'clock', '6 o\'clock', 'Σ (mean)']):\n",
    "    mask = data['dose'] != 1\n",
    "    ax.scatter(data[feature], data['chrom_total'], color='grey', label='All doses')\n",
    "    x = data.loc[mask, feature].to_numpy().reshape(-1, 1)\n",
    "    y = data.loc[mask, 'chrom_total'].to_numpy()\n",
    "    model = next(f['model'] for f in fits if f['feature'] == feature)\n",
    "    x_range = np.linspace(x.min(), x.max(), 100).reshape(-1, 1)\n",
    "    ax.scatter(x, y, color='tab:blue', label='Fit (dose≠1)')\n",
    "    ax.plot(x_range, model.predict(x_range), color='black')\n",
    "    ax.set_title(title)\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel('Occupancy')\n",
    "axes[0].set_ylabel('Chrom_total (mg·gDW⁻¹)')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Geometry Discussion\n",
    "Summarise the BRDF implications and orientation sensitivity referencing thesis discussion."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- 12 o'clock (near-nadir) shows the tightest linear relationship; off-nadir (6 o'clock) suffers greater scatter.\n",
    "- Σ aggregation (mean across orientations) reduces orientation dependence and is the recommended scalar.\n",
    "- Residual variance illustrates BRDF limitations noted on p.42; controlled geometry would further tighten the mapping."
   ]
  }
